# Go REST API Conventions

- Use package layout: handler -> service -> repository.
- Keep handlers thin: parse request, call service, write response.
- Put business logic in services, not handlers.
- Keep repository focused on DB queries only.
- Return clear errors and map them to proper HTTP status codes.
- Use context-aware methods for DB and external calls.
- Name methods and types clearly and consistently.
